        <options>
            <option letter="a">It relied only on volunteers</option>
            <option letter="b">It created a fair and efficient draft system</option>
            <option letter="c">It excluded minorities</option>
            <option letter="d">It only drafted officers</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Selective Service Act of 1917 created a more fair and efficient draft system than previous methods, requiring all men within certain age ranges to register regardless of social status.</explanation>
